In this article, President Donald J. Trump proclaims November 9, 2019, as World Freedom Day in commemoration of the fall of the Berlin Wall. The article highlights the significance of the wall's collapse as a victory for democratic principles and the end of the Cold War. It emphasizes the importance of freedom and individual liberty, stating that any system of government that impedes the rights of the people is destined to fail. The article also mentions the ongoing fight against oppression and the commitment of the United States to uphold democratic values. It pays tribute to those who helped liberate Eastern and Central Europe from communist oppression and reaffirms support for those pursuing freedom worldwide. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe World Freedom Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.